history.content:
Hi Julian,

Please also see @584 for Prof. Alon's advice on Math 53 and 54.

Many EECS students are opting to Phase II 16A since there are 200 reserved seats for you through Dec 10 and are using their Phase I for other classes. These reserved seats will be released on Dec 11. Also, keep in mind that the secondary sections will be more limited than if you use your Phase I units.

I am an EECS Sophomore (with junior seating), and I was planning on taking EE16A and Math 54 next semester, but then came across @556. Given this, is it better for me to put off taking 54 until a future semester? Will I be screwed on graduation requirements if I do that?

Also, I was planning on enrolling in 16A Phase 2, as there are reserved seats for EECS majors, is that going to be an issue?
